}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["2) Coherence factors", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9829351980629463`*^9, 
  3.982935213777409*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8d3a1c17-e404-4808-8f7b-\
789198db7cb1"],

Cell["\<\
Consider A1 decaying to a flavour eigenstate. 
Consider A2 decaying to two cases: 
a) CP eigenstate;
b) flavour eigenstate.
c) A1 and A2 decaying into flavour eigenstates with kinematic degrees of \
freedom
We look at a), b), and c) in turn.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.982939508308617*^9, {3.982940030008381*^9, 3.982940030512061*^9}, {
   3.983079302639946*^9, 
   3.983079332824429*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bcd1077a-0a21-4774-99d0-\
a939567dab75"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["a) CP eigenstate", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982940036075317*^9, 
  3.982940061435079*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6e777189-eac1-43aa-802a-\
9eeb7cd970f2"],

Cell["\<\
In this case A2 = either A2bar or -A2bar, therefore r2 = 1 and spd2 is either \
0 or pi.  Run it for spd2 for 0 (CPeven) and pi (CPodd) separately:\
\>", "Text",
