Cell["\<\
Same idea, but work with a special case and a general case. 
Special case is that the two sides are the same, for example Kpi v. Kpi. In \
this case, two cases can happen: either the kaon charge is identical, or the \
kaon charge is flipped. Neglecting DCS / charm mixing possibility, the equal \
case should be zero. Indeed,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982941164665263*^9, 3.98294129422196*^9}, {
  3.9829415093122253`*^9, 3.9829415106949453`*^9}, {3.982941588715144*^9, 
  3.9829415891589127`*^9}, {3.9829418216790867`*^9, 
  3.982941823652903*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4ca044ab-0b39-46e6-90d9-\
1fead9035843"],

